  <div class="container">

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <section id="overview">
      <h2>📋 Overview</h2>
      <p>This guide explains how to manage contacts in GoHighLevel (GHL) — including how to tag contacts individually or in bulk, how to create Smart Lists, how to export contacts to a CSV file, and how to import contacts from one GHL account to another.</p>

      <h3>Why Tagging Matters</h3>
      <p>Tags in GHL are labels attached to contacts that drive automation logic. When you apply a tag, it can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Trigger a workflow automatically</li>
        <li>Add a contact to a pipeline</li>
        <li>Filter contacts into Smart Lists</li>
        <li>Identify where a contact came from</li>
        <li>Exclude contacts from campaigns</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="info-box">
        💡 <strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> If a tag doesn't exist yet, GHL will create it the first time you type it. Always double-check spelling — tags are case sensitive.
      </div>

      <h3>The Florida → Hawaii Migration — What We Did</h3>
      <div class="flow-diagram">
        <div class="flow-box orange">Tag Florida contacts<br/><small>source_florida</small></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-box blue">Tag Hawaii contacts<br/><small>source_hawaii</small></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-box">Export Florida contacts<br/><small>CSV to hard drive</small></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-box green">Import into Hawaii GHL<br/><small>contacts merged</small></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW TO TAG A SINGLE CONTACT -->
    <section id="tagging">
      <h2>🏷️ How to Tag a Single Contact</h2>
      <p>Use this method when you need to tag one contact manually — for example to test a workflow before launching to the full list.</p>

      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to <strong>Contacts</strong> in the left sidebar</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><p>Search for the contact by name or phone number</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click on the contact to open their record</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><p>Scroll down to the <strong>Tags</strong> section on the right side panel</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>+ Add Tag</strong></p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">6</span><div class="step-content"><p>Type the tag name and select it from the dropdown or press Enter to create it</p><p class="step-note">Example: type <code>customer_3plus_years</code> to trigger the 3-Year Upgrade SMS workflow</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">7</span><div class="step-content"><p>The tag is applied immediately — if a workflow is triggered, it will fire within seconds</p></div></div>

      <div class="success-box" style="margin-top:16px;">
        ✅ <strong>Test tip:</strong> Always tag 2-3 test contacts individually before bulk tagging the full list. This lets you confirm the workflow fires correctly without affecting all contacts.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BULK TAGGING -->
    <section id="bulk-tag">
      <h2>🏷️🏷️ How to Bulk Tag Multiple Contacts</h2>
      <p>Use this method to apply a tag to a large group of contacts at once — for example when launching a campaign.</p>

      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to <strong>Contacts</strong> in the left sidebar</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><p>Use filters or open a <strong>Smart List</strong> to narrow down the contacts you want to tag</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click the <strong>checkbox at the top</strong> of the contacts list to select all visible contacts</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click the banner that appears: <strong>"Select all X contacts"</strong> — this selects every contact in the filtered list, not just those visible on screen</p><p class="step-note">Important: if you skip this step you will only tag the contacts visible on the current page</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Actions</strong> at the top of the page</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">6</span><div class="step-content"><p>Select <strong>Add Tag</strong></p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">7</span><div class="step-content"><p>Type the tag name and confirm</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">8</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Apply</strong> — all selected contacts are tagged immediately</p></div></div>

      <div class="warn-box">
        ⚠️ <strong>Be careful with bulk tagging.</strong> If the tag triggers a workflow, it will fire for every contact simultaneously. Always test on 2-3 contacts first.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SMART LISTS -->
    <section id="smart-list">
      <h2>📋 How to Create a Smart List</h2>
      <p>A Smart List is a saved filtered view of your contacts. It automatically updates as contacts meet or stop meeting the filter criteria.</p>

      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to <strong>Contacts</strong> in the left sidebar</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Smart Lists</strong> at the top of the page</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>+ New Smart List</strong></p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><p>Give it a clear name — for example: <strong>3+ Year Customers — Upgrade Ready</strong></p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Add Filter</strong> and set your conditions</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">6</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Save Smart List</strong></p></div></div>

      <h3>Common Filter Examples</h3>
      <table class="action-table">
        <thead><tr><th>What You Want</th><th>Filter Settings</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Contacts inactive for 3+ years</td><td>Last Activity → Is → More than → 3 → Years → Ago</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Contacts with a specific tag</td><td>Tags → includes → [tag name]</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Exclude contacts with a tag</td><td>Tags → does not include → [tag name]</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Contacts from a specific source</td><td>Tags → includes → source_florida OR source_hawaii</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <!-- EXPORTING CONTACTS -->
    <section id="export">
      <h2>📤 How to Export Contacts from GHL</h2>
      <p>Use this to download a list of contacts to your computer as a CSV file — for backup, migration, or importing into another GHL account.</p>

      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to <strong>Contacts</strong> in the left sidebar</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><p>Filter or open a Smart List to show only the contacts you want to export</p><p class="step-note">Example: open the Smart List filtered by tag <code>source_florida</code> to export only Florida contacts</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click the <strong>checkbox at the top</strong> to select all visible contacts</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>"Select all X contacts"</strong> to select the entire filtered list</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Actions</strong> at the top</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">6</span><div class="step-content"><p>Select <strong>Export</strong></p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">7</span><div class="step-content"><p>GHL will prepare the CSV file and send a download link to your email — check your inbox</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">8</span><div class="step-content"><p>Download the CSV file and save it to your hard drive</p></div></div>

      <div class="info-box">
        💡 The exported CSV will include all contact fields — name, email, phone, tags, and custom fields. Keep it in a safe location as it contains patient data.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- IMPORTING CONTACTS -->
    <section id="import">
      <h2>📥 How to Import Contacts into GHL</h2>
      <p>Use this to upload a CSV file of contacts into a GHL account — for example when migrating contacts from Florida into the Hawaii account.</p>

      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to <strong>Contacts</strong> in the left sidebar</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click the <strong>Import</strong> button at the top right (looks like an upload icon)</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Upload CSV</strong> and select the file from your hard drive</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><p>GHL will show a field mapping screen — match your CSV columns to GHL fields</p><p class="step-note">Example: match "First Name" column → First Name field, "Phone" column → Phone field</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><p>Scroll down and look for the <strong>Tags</strong> option — you can apply a tag to all imported contacts at this step</p><p class="step-note">Example: apply <code>source_florida</code> so you know these contacts came from the Florida account</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">6</span><div class="step-content"><p>Click <strong>Import</strong> to begin the upload</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">7</span><div class="step-content"><p>GHL will process the import — you will receive a notification when complete</p></div></div>
      <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">8</span><div class="step-content"><p>Go to Contacts and search or filter by <code>source_florida</code> to confirm all contacts imported correctly</p></div></div>

      <div class="warn-box">
        ⚠️ <strong>Check for duplicates.</strong> If a contact already exists in GHL with the same phone number or email, GHL will merge the records rather than create duplicates. Review the import report to confirm.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- REAL EXAMPLE -->
    <section id="real-example">
      <h2>✅ Real Example — Florida to Hawaii Migration</h2>
      <p>Here is exactly what was done to migrate Florida contacts into the Hawaii GHL account:</p>

      <h3>Step 1 — Tag Florida Contacts</h3>
      <p>In the Florida GHL account, all contacts were tagged with <span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span> so they could be easily identified and filtered for export.</p>

      <h3>Step 2 — Tag Hawaii Contacts</h3>
      <p>In the Hawaii GHL account, all existing contacts were tagged with <span class="tag-pill tag-hawaii">source_hawaii</span> to distinguish them from incoming Florida contacts.</p>

      <h3>Step 3 — Export Florida Contacts</h3>
      <p>In the Florida GHL account, the Smart List filtered by <span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span> was used to select all Florida contacts and export them as a CSV file to the hard drive.</p>

      <h3>Step 4 — Import into Hawaii GHL</h3>
      <p>The CSV file was uploaded into the Hawaii GHL account using the Import function. The <span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span> tag was applied during import so all incoming contacts were immediately identifiable.</p>

      <div class="success-box">
        ✅ <strong>Result:</strong> Both contact groups are now in the Hawaii GHL account and can be targeted independently using their source tags — <span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span> for Florida contacts and <span class="tag-pill tag-hawaii">source_hawaii</span> for Hawaii contacts.
      </div>

      <h3>How to Filter by Source in Future Campaigns</h3>
      <table class="action-table">
        <thead><tr><th>If you want to target...</th><th>Filter by tag...</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Florida contacts only</td><td><span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Hawaii contacts only</td><td><span class="tag-pill tag-hawaii">source_hawaii</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>All contacts</td><td>No tag filter needed</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Exclude Florida contacts</td><td>Tags does not include <span class="tag-pill tag-florida">source_florida</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Exclude Hawaii contacts</td><td>Tags does not include <span class="tag-pill tag-hawaii">source_hawaii</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <!-- TAG REFERENCE -->
    <section id="tag-reference">
      <h2>📌 HBS Tag Reference</h2>
      <p>Here is a reference of all active tags in GHL and what they are used for:</p>
      <table class="action-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Tag</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Triggers Workflow?</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>source_florida</code></td><td>Contact originated from the Florida GHL account</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>source_hawaii</code></td><td>Contact is an original Hawaii GHL contact</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>customer_3plus_years</code></td><td>Triggers the 3-Year Upgrade SMS Campaign</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>opted_out</code></td><td>Contact replied STOP — do not contact</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>th_transition_2026</code></td><td>Triggers the True Hearing Transition email campaign</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>true hearing</code></td><td>Existing TruHearing patient (~96 contacts)</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>true hearing one year</code></td><td>TruHearing patient less than 1 year (~21 contacts)</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>sold</code></td><td>Sale completed — excluded from upgrade campaigns</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>warm_lead_old</code></td><td>Previous warm lead from prior contact</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>repair_inquiry</code></td><td>Contact inquired about device repair</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>long_term_nurture</code></td><td>Interested but not ready — in drip sequence</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>consult_booked</code></td><td>Consultation appointment booked</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>consult_completed</code></td><td>Consultation has been completed</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>quote_sent</code></td><td>Quote has been sent to contact</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>group_offer_church</code></td><td>Church or community group offer</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>group_offer_family</code></td><td>Family group offer</td><td>No</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

